    "reasoning": "(a) **Time left until resolution**\n\nToday is July 3, 2026. The resolution date is September 2026 (approximately 2 months remaining).\n\n(b) **Status quo outcome if nothing changes**\n\nBased on the research provided, Claude Mythos is currently available only to a limited set of ~150 approved organizations as of June 2026. \"Claude Fable 5\" was released publicly on June 9, 2026, but Claude Mythos remains restricted. If nothing changes, Claude Mythos will remain unavailable to the general public through September 2026.\n\n(c) **Scenario for NO outcome**\n\nAnthropic continues its current strategy of keeping Claude Mythos in limited preview/beta access for approved customers only through September 2026. The company may feel no commercial, technical, or strategic pressure to make a full public release before the deadline. This is consistent with cautious AI deployment practices.\n\n(d) **Scenario for YES outcome**\n\nAnthropic decides to transition Claude Mythos from limited preview to public release (similar to how Claude Fable 5 was made public in June). This could happen due to:\n- Successful performance data from the ~150 beta organizations\n- Competitive pressure from other AI labs\n- Strategic decision that the model is safe enough for wider deployment\n- Commercial timing or partnership announcements\n\n(e) **Base rate**\n\nNo reliable base rate available \u2014 proceeding on priors.\n\nHowever, I can note: AI models typically take months to transition from limited preview to public release. The fact that Claude Mythos has been in limited preview since April 2026 (3+ months) and Anthropic chose to release \"Claude Fable 5\" publicly instead (rather than expanding Mythos access) suggests organizational preference for a cautious, staged rollout. Large capability model releases typically follow careful evaluation periods.\n\n(f) **How the live research moves me from priors**\n\nThe research is crucial here. It shows:\n- Claude Mythos was introduced in \"limited preview\" on April 7, 2026\n- As of June 2, access was expanded to 150 organizations\n- On June 9, Anthropic released \"Claude Fable 5\" publicly, while keeping \"Claude Mythos 5\" restricted to approved customers only\n- Access was temporarily disabled mid-June, then restrictions were lifted\n\nThis pattern suggests Anthropic is deliberately maintaining a two-tiered approach: a public tier (Fable 5) and a limited tier (Mythos 5). The fact that they *explicitly chose not to make Mythos public* on June 9 when they released Fable 5 is important negative evidence. This suggests they had the opportunity and consciously decided against it.\n\n(g) **How my view has changed since the original 29% forecast**\n\nThe original forecast at 29% appears reasonable given:\n- We are now only ~2 months from resolution (vs. ~5 months when the original forecast was made)\n- The research shows Anthropic made an explicit choice NOT to release Mythos publicly in early June\n- The company appears committed to a gradual, cautious release strategy\n- There is no indication of imminent public launch in the research\n\nThe previous forecaster likely weighted: historical tech company behavior (models do eventually go public), against: recent negative signal (choosing not to release in June), and time constraints (only 2 months left).\n\nI would expect the probability to remain roughly stable or shift slightly downward, since we've now seen Anthropic's recent decision-making and they chose the conservative path.\n\n(h) **Divergence from community prediction**\n\nThe current community prediction is 31% (provided in the question). My analysis aligns closely with this, suggesting minor adjustment downward but not substantially departing from the consensus view. The community appears well-calibrated to the negative signal from Anthropic's June decision to keep Mythos restricted.\n\n**Reasoning for my estimate:**\n\n- **Time constraint:** Only 2 months remain; tech releases require planning and announcement lead time\n- **Recent negative signal:** Anthropic explicitly chose not to release Mythos publicly in June despite having the opportunity\n- **Organizational pattern:** The two-tiered approach (public Fable, restricted Mythos) suggests deliberate strategy\n- **Upside scenario (~25-30%):** Possible that strong positive beta results motivate an accelerated public release in the next 8 weeks, or that \"similar model\" language in the question allows for broader interpretation\n- **Downside scenario (~70-75%):** Current limited preview approach continues through September\n\nThe prior 29% forecast appears well-reasoned. Given we now have the negative signal of Anthropic's June decision and shorter time remaining, I make a modest downward adjustment.\n\n**Probability: 28%**",
    "research_text": "I found no internal contradictions in this summary. The timeline is internally consistent:\n\n- April 7: Claude Mythos introduced in limited preview\n- June 2: Access expanded to 150 organizations\n- June 9: Claude Fable 5 released publicly; Claude Mythos 5 launched for approved customers only\n- Mid-June: Access disabled, then restrictions lifted\n\nThe distinction between the publicly available Claude Fable 5 and the limited-availability Claude Mythos 5 is clearly maintained throughout.\n\n**Summary returned UNCHANGED, word-for-word.**",
